Photo_description: A “Gypsy camp” in the Berlin district of Marzahn. In an unpublicized “clean-up” of the city, the German Ministry of the Interior ordered the Berlin Chief of Police to arrest and intern approximately 800 Roma and Sinti on July 16 1936. The camp would later serve as a site for deportations to Auschwitz.
